      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI B NZ (9) started a hot favourite at his latest appearance and led but faded late to fourth. That was his first outing for nearly seven weeks and he had been racing well in Sydney prior so he is capable of a much better performance. CO CAPTAIN (1) hasn't raced since he finished seventh at Listed level at Melton in February but had been showing promise prior with top-two finishes in his four others starts, winning two of them. Gets the ace draw for his return and was readied with three nice trials so could work through his grades this time in. TIVOLI (10) took her record at this circuit and distance to two from three when winning from this row last week. Must respect. OLLIES THE BOSS (6) is first up for five-and-a-half months but races well fresh and has placed in two Melton trials so could open this campaign with a positive effort.",
